{
  "text": "To investigate the properties of Ad-P450 cells, we performed kinetic analyses using P450 substrates and calculated IC 50 values for specific representative P450 inhibitors (CYP1A2, furafylline; CYP2C9, sulfaphenazole; CYP2C19, ticlopidine; CYP2D6, quinidine; CYP3A4, ketoconazole) in Ad-P450 cells (Figs. 2 and 3) . The Michaelis-Menten equation was used to calculate the Km and Vmax values from the metabolic reaction rates of the five P450s ( Table 2 ). The specific P450 inhibitors used showed concentrationdependent inhibition, and the IC 50 values are shown in Table 2 . These values are similar to those previously reported [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . These results suggest that Ad-P450 cells are useful for the assessment of P450-mediated drug metabolism, and drug-drug or health food-drug interactions.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "20946027",
